sql:
SELECT p.name, phr.next_review_date
FROM patients p
JOIN patient_health_risks phr ON p.patient_id = phr.patient_id;

SELECT DISTINCT p.name AS patient_name
FROM patients p
JOIN patient_hcp_assignments pha ON p.patient_id = pha.patient_id;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT patient_id) AS total_patients
FROM patient_hcp_assignments
WHERE patient_id NOT IN (
    SELECT patient_id
    FROM patient_treatments
);

external_knowledge:
A patient's health risk profile refers to the collection of health risks associated with a patient; Health risks are conditions or factors that may affect a patient's well-being or health; 
Treatment options are the recommended actions or interventions to mitigate or manage health risks; 
The results are ordered to facilitate easy reference and comparison across patients and their associated health risks.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT patient_id) 
FROM patient_hcp_assignments 
WHERE relationship = 'primary care physician';

SELECT AVG(pt.adherence) AS average_adherence
FROM patient_treatments pt
INNER JOIN patient_hcp_assignments pa ON pt.patient_id = pa.patient_id;
